      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Tonning. ¶  22nd. March 1841. ¶ My dear Ferdinand ¶  ¶ Wondered when I would get your next letter, regret my visit to Husum postponed, I wanted to see Marie Klauders ... ¶  ¶ I have one request to mak...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">41.03.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Iwanne Müller</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found. The text given here was 'Translated in Sydney from the German', and placed in Louise Wehl's scrap-book.</p>
               </note>Tonning.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Tönning.</p>
               </note> 22nd. March 1841.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Ferdinand</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wondered when I would get your next letter, regret my visit to Husum postponed, I wanted to see Marie Klauders ...<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">translator's elision.</seg> The name has probably been misread by the translator, Iwanne probably wrote 'Klanders'. The Klander family of Husum, including M's Latin tutor Albrecht Klander, was related to Magdalene Mertens.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have one request to make to you. Bertha asked in her letter, for you to come to her Confirmation. Please dear Ferdinand do not be so particular about taking time off. You surely can have another 8 days at time of horse market — bed and everything ready, only you missing! Now you have been at Husum nearly a year. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A fortnight after Easter we are ceasing to wear mourning.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">For their mother, Louise Müller, who died 15 April 1840.</p>
               </note> Expect you will go on another quarter.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferdinand I think Bertha has to go to Hamburg to learn Millinery and dressmaking. I think everything will be sold — but do not tell Uncle I wrote this. Theodore<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Theodor Müller?</p>
               </note> was here on business, he had an idea of taking the ferries, but Uncle gave no hope. As long as he had land in Ditmarsch he would not let the ferries out of his hand, as families had to be considered.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Whether business is going to pieces or not do not know. Theodore says many forwarding agents are looking for nice business — because the Channel business is bad. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Wilhelm</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg style="">Not identified.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline"> has acquired a bride and they consider him very handsome. </hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am practising Fortepiano a lot amongst other things "Futuna Gallop" "Sleep Walker's Waltz" and "Brothers Run" gallop. This week we have a young people's ball. Karl Weber has a position in Heurburg<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Harburg, adjacent to and now part of Hamburg?</p>
               </note> — an important one Salary 50 (something)<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">(something) <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is the translator's note.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I do not know if I shall go to the ball. I do not know why Uncle wants me to stay at home, Uncle and Aunt are going. </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With love</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Iwanne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Bertha sends love.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
